A. True
In Terraform, the required_providers block (inside the terraform {} block) is the only place where you ever reference a provider by its full source address and version constraint. Example:
hclterraform {
  required_providers {
    aws = {
      source  = "hashicorp/aws"
      version = "~> 5.0"
    }
  }
}
Everywhere else in the configuration — resource blocks, data sources, provider configuration blocks, provider meta-arguments, modules, etc. — Terraform uses only the local name (the key from required_providers, which defaults to the provider type if the block is omitted)
